hopobject.name: Page
hopobject.body: I do some voluntary work illegal possession of prescription drugs indiana Featherstone, 46, maintains that the job is less daunting than setting up the National Theatre of Scotland in 2006, which was a widely hailed triumph, even if some north of the border took this Surrey-raised interloper to task for a perceived Anglocentric neglect of the Scottish canon, a campaign of criticism she describes as “bullying”. She detects little added pressure, too, from being the Court’s first female artistic director: “If this was the 1970s it might be different but I feel I’ve been around a powerful generation of women since I was born.”
